ed for studies on this subject, in order to better understand the mechanisms of co-evolution between this group of bacteria and their vertebrate hosts. The role of neotropical bat-associated Neorickettsia sp. and bats from Brazil in the biological cycle of such agent warrant further investigation.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "De Mello, Vict\u00f3ria Valente Califre", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Placa, Ana Julia Vidal", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lee, Daniel Antonio Braga", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Franco, Eliz Oliveira", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lima, Luciana", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Teixeira, Marta M.G.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hemsley, Claudia", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Titball, Richard W.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Machado, Rosangela Zacarias", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Andr\u00e9, Marcos Rog\u00e9rio", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/77565fe8cdddd83b2ba49392c6e9422f", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/3b55492f6ba6abd0956a4651b79dce1e67d28770362117c6da2d829e1400e5f7", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/7GIPEV8J", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/7GIPEV8J", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/a659d297fd263d13982685bae98add7e!/b134040-136510", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["